# Contributing

Refer to the [Ansible community guide](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/devel/community/index.html).

## This repository

- **Run the tests.** Unit tests: `pytest` (from the repo root). Molecule:
  `make molecule` for the full suite, `make molecule SCENARIO=<name>` for one
  scenario (boots a QEMU RouterOS CHR — see `extensions/molecule/README.md`).
  CI runs the same make targets.
- **Add a changelog fragment.** Every user-facing PR needs a fragment in
  `changelogs/fragments/` ([antsibull-changelog
  format](https://ansible.readthedocs.io/projects/antsibull-changelog/changelogs/));
  the `changelog` CI job gates the merge on it.
- **Keep code and release PRs separate.** Version bumps (`galaxy.yml`,
  changelog regeneration) ship in their own `chore(release)` PR, not with the
  change itself.
- **Pure block-style YAML everywhere** — no inline `{}`/`[]` flow collections
  (see `AGENTS.md`).
